example.disclaimerText: The search executed is based on data that you have selected.  Your search is not a request for prior authorization and is not notification to UnitedHealthcare.  Prior authorization requirements vary by benefit plan and the provider's participation status.  Your search does not guarantee coverage.  Coverage determinations are based on the member's benefit plan and eligibility for benefits, in addition to other criteria.  This tool is intended to check requirements for Medical services only.  Behavioral Health requirements must be verified through www.ProviderExpress.com.  For Home and Community Based Services, please call the number on the back of the member's ID card.  Note that prior authorization requirements for Oxford members are not currently supported on this tool.  UnitedHealthcare Exchange Plan member benefits must be verified through www.UHCProvider.com/exchanges.

benefits.benefitDetails: What are hearing aids? Hearing aids are electronic amplifying devices designed to bring sound more effectively into the ear. A hearing aid consists of a microphone, amplifier and receiver. Benefits are provided for the hearing aid and charges for fitting and testing as recommended by a doctor. UnitedHealthcare Hearing is available to you. For more information about this program, click here or call toll-free at 1-855-523-9355. TTY users can dial 711. Want more information? View the glossary for definitions.

limitsAndExceptions.details:
No coverage for bone anchored hearing aids except when:
  • Craniofacial anomalies or absent ear canals keep them from using a wearable hearing aid; or
  • Hearing loss cannot be improved by a wearable hearing aid.
If you meet the above criteria, benefits are limited to 1bone anchored hearing aid during the time you are enrolled under the policy. Repairs and/or replacements are not covered, except for malfunction.

post.description:
This service returns the basic eligibility information based on the member's plan.This includes (but is not limited to) the member's demographic information, plan level cost shares, plan coverage details and insurance details.

Search Options and required search fields:
MemberIDDateOfBirth requires: memberId, dateOfBirth.
MemberIDLastNameDateOfBirth requires: memberId, lastName, dateOfBirth.
MemberIDFirstNameDateOfBirth requires: memberId, firstName, dateOfBirth.
MemberIDName requires: memberId, firstName, lastName.
MemberIDNameDateOfBirth requires: memberId, firstName, lastName, dateOfBirth.
MemberIDNameGroupNumberDateOfBirth requires: memberId, firstName, lastName, groupNumber, dateOfBirth NameDateOfBirth requres: firstName, lastName, dateOfBirth.

Response Information:
*  lineOfBusinessCode - Determine which LineofBusiness the member belong to , we fetch this value from the Elig V4 service. Possible value are E&I, M&R and C&S.
*  TieringStatus - Determine which TieringStatus the member belongs to. We fetch this value from the 271 service in the service level.

Note:
This API will pull information related to Payer IDs: 87726, 06111, 25463, 37602, 39026, 74227, 65088, 81400, 03432, 86050, 86047, 95378, 95467, LIFE1 and WELM2.

post.description:
This service returns the case manager contact information assigned to C&S members. Transaction ID from Eligibility Information response is a required request parameter. If you are using member search parameters (memberId, dateOfBirth, firstName, firstDateOfService, lastDateOfService, familyIndicator, PayerId), all the parameters are required.

Note:

post.description:
This service returns the front image of the member's identification card. Transaction ID from Eligibility Information response is a required request parameter.If you are using member search parameters (memberId, dateOfBirth, firstName, planStartDate, planEndDate,familyIndicator), all the parameters are required.

Response Header Information:
*  backlength: Indicates the length of backside of the ID card. It is comma separated for UHONE and UHOne facets where we get more than 1 ID card.
*  cardsLength: It is comma separated value for UHONE and UHOne facets with the format image1.frontLength , image1.backLength , image2.frontLength , image2.backLength where we get more than 1 ID card.
*  numberOfCards: This value gives the total number of cards returned for UHONE and UHOne facets.
*  Content-Length: This value holds the value of entire content length.
*  frontlength: Indicates the length of frontside of the ID card. It is comma separated for UHONE and UHOne facets where we get more than 1 ID card.
*  Content-Type: This api returns image/png as content type.

Note: This API will pull information related to Payer IDs: 87726, 06111, 25463, 65088, 03432, 86050, 86047, 37602, 95378 and 95467.

memberId.description: The MemberID is conditional. MemberId is required if the search option is MemberIDOnly, MemberID, MemberIDDateOfBirth, MemberIDLastNameDateOfBirth, MemberIDFirstNameDateOfBirth, MemberIDName, MemberIDNameDateOfBirth, or MemberIDNameGroupNumberDateOfBirth.

policyNumber.description: The Member policyNumber is numeric. PolicyNumber is from any member search versions

dateOfBirth.description: Member's DateOfBirth. Date format YYYY-MM-DD. DateOfBirth is conditional. DateOfBirth is required if the search option is MemberIDDateOfBirth, MemberIDNameGroupNumberDateOfBirth, MemberIDLastNameDateOfBirth, MemberIDFirstNameDateOfBirth, MemberIDNameDateOfBirth, or NameDateOfBirth.

firstName.description: The Member FirstName. FirstName is conditional.  FirstName is required If the search option is MemberIDFirstNameDateOfBirth or MemberIDName

firstDateOfService.description: Member coverage start date. Date format YYYY-MM-DD. Default takes current date. FirstDateOfService is conditional

lastDateOfService.description: Member coverage end date. Date format YYYY-MM-DD. Default takes current date. LastDateOfService is conditional

transactionId.description: TransactionId or member search parameters (memberId, dateOfBirth, firstName, firstDateOfService, lastDateOfService, familyIndicator) are required . TransactionId from any membersearch versions

needAddlPolicyInfo.description: Based on the needAddlPolicyInfo value(true/false) the service will return the AdditionalPolicy Information

policyId.description: The member's PolicyId comes from Elig V3

planStartDate.description: Member's coverage start date. Date format YYYY-MM-DD. Default takes current date.

planEndDate.description: Member's coverage end date. Date format YYYY-MM-DD. Default takes current date.

transactionId.description: TransactionId from any member search versions. TransactionId is conditional; either TransactionId or PatientKey must be passed in the request.

patientKey.description: PatientKey from any member search versions. PatientKey is conditional; either PatientKey or TransactionId must be passed in the request.
PatientKey from any member search versions. PatientKey is conditional; either PatientKey or TransactionId must be passed in the request.

serviceTypeCodes.description: ServiceTypeCodes to identify the service. ServiceTypeCodes is conditional; either ServiceTypeCodes or ServiceTypeDescriptions must be passed in the request.

serviceTypeDescriptions.description: The service type descriptions. ServiceTypeDescriptions is conditional; either ServiceTypeDescriptions or ServiceTypeCodes must be passed in the request.

policyId.description: The policyId comes form Elig v3
